  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation like this can be difficult and emotionally charged. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Take some time to process your emotions. How do you feel about her actions and the relationship? Understanding your feelings can help you communicate more clearly.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: Consider having an honest conversation with her. Share your feelings about the situation and ask her about it. Understanding her perspective can provide clarity.\n\n3. **Evaluate the Relationship**: Think about what you want moving forward. Are you willing to work through this, or do you think it's a dealbreaker? Assess what\u2019s best for you both in terms of the relationship.\n\n4. **Set Boundaries**: If you decide to continue the relationship, discuss boundaries and what trust means moving forward. Clear communication about expectations can help rebuild trust.\n\n5. **Take Your Time**: Don\u2019t rush into a decision. Whether it\u2019s reconciling or moving on, take the time you need to consider your options.\n\n6. **Seek Support**: Talk to friends, family, or a counselor who can provide support as you navigate your feelings and decisions.\n\nUltimately, it's essential to prioritize your well-being and make a choice that feels right for you.",
